definitions.definition: Ellipsis of the Mediterranean Sea : a sea between Europe and Africa , an inland branch of the Atlantic .
A region of Southern Europe and North Africa and Western Asia . The region surrounding the Mediterranean Sea.

main_definition: Ellipsis of the Mediterranean Sea : a sea between Europe and Africa , an inland branch of the Atlantic .
secondary_definitions: A region of Southern Europe and North Africa and Western Asia . The region surrounding the Mediterranean Sea.

definitions.definition: Ellipsis of Mediterranean food , a style of food originating from the (often European or Near Eastern , as opposed to African) lands surrounding the Mediterranean Sea .

secondary_definitions: ( uncountable ) Ellipsis of Mediterranean food , a style of food originating from the (often European or Near Eastern , as opposed to African) lands surrounding the Mediterranean Sea .
